title: Cross country poll: Lady Lex unanimous No. 1
text:
Cross country poll: Lady Lex unanimous No. 1 Staff report 10:55 a.m. EDT October 21, 2015 STK Stock CONNECT 2 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
COLUMBUS - A week after losing a first-place vote in the state coaches poll to Kettering Alter, Lexingtonâ€™s girls cross country team got its vote back and is again the unanimous No. 1 team in Division II. 
The Lexington boys are ranked third in Division II, while the Colonel Crawford boys are No. 3 in Division III. 
Others appearing in the poll were Fredericktown at seventh, Mapleton at 14th and Mount Gilead at 15th in Division III boys with Northmor 11th, Fredericktown 12th and Mount Gilead 15th in Division III girls. Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1LLrORo MORE STORIES
